{
  "texts": [
    "By analyzing seven major events in CAISO, we identify distinct regional inertia characteristics, including elevated RoCoF values, earlier inertial response arrival times, and lower regional inertia during midday disturbances.",
    "These variations often correspond to reduced net load resulting from high solar output and evolving system dynamics.",
    "Our results show a declining inertia trend through 2018, followed by a recovery phase likely supported by growing deployment of front-of-the-meter BESS and grid-forming controls.",
    "Despite these improvements, spatial imbalances persist.",
    "These findings reinforce the importance of region-specific inertia monitoring, dynamic situational awareness, and adaptive control strategies to maintain frequency stability during the grid transition."
  ]
}